   <section id="multi-cloud-challenges">
    <div class="g-container">
     <img alt="Multi Cloud Illustration" src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/2885/1507304058-multi-cloud-illustration.svg"/>
     <div class="g-section-header">
      <h2>
       The challenge
       <span class="darken">
        of going multi-cloud
       </span>
      </h2>
      <h3 class="g-text">
       The shift from
       <strong>
        static and consolidated
       </strong>
       to
       <strong>
        dynamic and distributed
       </strong>
       infrastructure introduces challenges for the key people that manage infrastructure:
      </h3>
     </div>
     <ul class="g-callouts">
      <li>
       <h5>
        Operations
       </h5>
       The challenge for operations teams moving to cloud is to enable the automation through infrastructure as code while embracing the inevitable heterogeneity of different cloud providers.
      </li>
      <li>
       <h5>
        Security
       </h5>
       The challenge for security professionals is to rethink the 'castle &amp; moat' approach to perimeter-based security and reconsider security holistically across the dynamic, distributed fleet.
      </li>
      <li>
       <h5>
        Architects &amp; developers
       </h5>
       The challenge for architects and developers is to accommodate the necessary diversity of application platforms across a distributed fleet.
      </li>
     </ul>
    </div>
   </section>
